http Request:
-------------
How to create a new client?
	-> client, client := &http.Client{ CheckRedirect: redirectPolicyFunc, }
	
How to fetch info from an url using that client?
	-> resp, err := client.Get("http://example.com")
	
How to create a new request?
	-> req, err := http.NewRequest("GET", "http://example.com", nil)
	
How to modify the request created?
	-> req.Header.Add("If-None-Match", `W/"wyzzy"`)
	-> resp, err := client.Do(req)	
	
MongoDB Installation
--------------------
Link : https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu/
1. wget -qO - https://www.mongodb.org/static/pgp/server-4.4.asc | sudo apt-key add -

2. To check the version of ubuntu,
	hari@hari-Vostro-3550:~/go/src$ lsb_release -dc
		Description:	Ubuntu 20.04.1 LTS
		Codename:	focal

3. echo "deb [ arch=amd64,arm64 ] https://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu focal/mongodb-org/4.4 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-4.4.list

4. sudo apt-get update
5. sudo apt-get install -y mongodb-org

6. To check whether to use systemd or system V init, type the below command
	-> ps --no-headers -o comm 1
		systemd
		
7. To start/stop/restart the mongodb
	-> sudo systemctl start mongod
	-> sudo systemctl stop mongod
	-> sudo systemctl restart mongod
	-> sudo systemctl status mongod


successful mongodb install: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu-tarball/
	-> once you run mongodb, check mongod.log to check if connection is accepted or ended
	
To run Mongodb:
	1. mongod --dbpath /var/lib/mongo --logpath /var/log/mongodb/mongod.log --fork
	2. mongo

Get goLang Libraries,
	-> go get gopkg.in/mgo.v2
	-> go get gopkg.in/mgo.v2/bson
	
MongoDB insert a user:
	-> curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"Name":"Hari","Gender":"Male","Age":31,"Id":"1234567"}' http://localhost:8000/user/
		{"Name":"Hari","Gender":"Male","Age":31,"Id":"60d95350c4ad8e6c9d28d97b"}
		
	-> Another user : 60d953a0c4ad8e6c9d28d97c
	
	-> To retrieve the use :
		-> curl http://localhost:8000/user/60d95350c4ad8e6c9d28d97b

MongoDB TroubleShooting page
-----------------------------
	-> https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/installation-ubuntu-community-troubleshooting/
	-> https://stackoverflow.com/questions/51417708/unable-to-install-mongodb-properly-on-ubuntu-18-04-lts
	
	-> To remove the complete mongo installed in ubuntu
		* sudo apt-get purge mongodb-org*
		
MongoDB commands:
	refer the link: https://www.tutorialspoint.com/mongodb/mongodb_quick_guide.htm#:~:text=To%20get%20stats%20about%20MongoDB,and%20documents%20in%20the%20database
	1. To show the list of dbs
		* show dbs
	2. To use a collection (for example to use a collection "test")
		* use test
	3. To list the list of all records in a collection
		* db.<dbname>.find()
		* Like, db.test.find(); test is the collection name
		
	4. To display the result in a formatted way,
		* db.<dbname>.find().pretty()
		
	5. How to query a collection based on name
		* db.users.find({"name":"James Bond"})
		
	6. Query a collection based on an id,
		* db.users.find({"id":ObjectId("60d95516c4ad8e77a4966d6e")})
		
	7. Query a colletion based on both name and id,
		* db.users.find({$and:[{"id":ObjectId("60d95516c4ad8e77a4966d6e")}, {"name":"James Bond"}]})
			########## keyword and is used ###############
	
